PARTIAL PLOT - ordinal forest

var.names_cat=c("gender", "immig")
var.names_cont0=c("grade", "video_games", "internet_quality", "internet_availability", "SCHRISK", "BULLIED", "BELONG", "COOPAGR", "TEACHSUP", "FAMSUP", "PERSEVAGR", "ASSERAGR", "EMPATAGR", "EMOCOAGR", "STRESAGR", "CURIOAGR", "math_time", "study_time", "MISCED", "FISCED", "HISCED", "ESCS")

for (i in 1:length(var.names_cat)) {
    xv <- forest.data[,var.names_cat[i]]
    x.pt <- levels(xv)
    y.pt <- numeric(length(x.pt))
    n <- nrow(forest.data) 
    ylab <- c("p(x=1)","p(x=2)","p(x=3)")
    par(mfrow=c(1,3))
    for (j in 1:3) {
      for (k in seq(along = x.pt)) {
        focus <- j #class (of y)
        x.data <- forest.data
        x.data[, var.names_cat[i]] <- factor(rep(x.pt[k], n), levels = x.pt)
        pr <- predict(ordforest.0, x.data, type = "prob")$classprobs
        y.pt[k] <- mean(pr[, focus])
      }
      barplot(y.pt, width=rep(1, length(y.pt)), col="blue",
              xlab = var.names_cat[i], ylab = ylab[j], names.arg=x.pt)
    }
}

for (i in 1:length(var.names_cont0)) {
    xv <- forest.data[,var.names_cont0[i]]
    xv <- as.numeric(xv)
    n.pt <- 20
    x.pt <- seq(min(xv), max(xv), length = n.pt)
    y.pt <- numeric(length(x.pt))
    n <- nrow(forest.data) 
    ylab <- c("p(x=1)","p(x=2)","p(x=3)")
    par(mfrow=c(1,3))
    for (j in 1:3) {
     for (k in seq(along = x.pt)) {
       focus <- j #class (of y)
       x.data <- forest.data
       x.data[, var.names_cont0[i]] <- rep(x.pt[k], n)
       pr <- predict(ordforest.0, x.data, type = "prob")$classprobs
       y.pt[k] <- mean(pr[, focus])
     }
     plot(x.pt, y.pt, type = "l", xlab=var.names_cont0[i], ylab=ylab[j])
    }
